                                <condition>The top end of the stone is broken off. Macalister (1945, 17) notes that the edge of the stone had been exposed to wear before being reused as a lintel and the <q>vowels are almost completely effaced</q>, but some of the other ogham characters can be determined.</condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout style="vertical" rend="arris_up">The inscription is on the angle. The visible portion extends beyond and into the side wall of the passage. </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>The inscription appears to have been <rs type="execution"  key="pocked" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/11.html">pocked</rs>. <height></height>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
