                        <provenance type="found" when="1864">Found reused as a lintel in the souterrain, known as Oweynagat ('the cave of the cats'), which is part of the larger complex of monuments at Rathcroghan. This ogham-inscribed lintel is at the entrance to the now blind passage to the right after entering the souterrain. The inscription was first discovered by Ferguson in 1864.</provenance>
                        <provenance type="observed">In situ as a lintel to the right inside the entrance to the souterrain at Oweynagat cave.
