    <text>
        <body>
             <div type="edition" subtype="ogham" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" resp="#POC">              
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/><persName>̣<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="stroke"/><w type="formula" lemma="maqqas" cert="low"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">ᚋᚐ</supplied>ᚊ</w> <name nymRef="#?" cert="low">ᚏ<unclear reason="worn">ᚓ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ᚐ</supplied>ᚄ</name> <w type="formula" lemma="muccoviias">ᚋᚒ<supplied reason="lost">ᚉᚑᚔ</supplied></w> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="stroke"/></persName>
                </ab> 
            </div>                    
            <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" xml:space="preserve" resp="#POC">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/><persName>̣<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="stroke"/><w type="formula" lemma="maqqas" cert="low"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">MA</supplied>Q</w> <name nymRef="#?" cert="low">R<unclear reason="worn">E</unclear><supplied reason="lost">A</supplied>S</name> <w type="formula" lemma="muccoviias">MU<supplied reason="lost">COI</supplied></w> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="stroke"/></persName>
                </ab>
                <ab type="list">[---MA(?)]Q REG[A]S MU[COI ---]</ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                <app n="1">  
                    <note>The inscription is too incomplete to enable a confident reading, but the above reconstruction might be suggested. The MU of a possible MUCOI is in a position inaccessible for photography or 3d imaging. </note>
                </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>The inscription likely follows the formula X son of Y family of...</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                 <p>The inscription might contain two common formula words MAQ for 'son' and MUCOI may be related to Early OIr. <distinct xml:lang="sga"><ref target="https://dil.ie/31187">moccu, maccu</ref></distinct> ‘belonging to the gens or family of’.</p>
            </div>
